tr: an alternative that is not available

value.def: Something that is impossible cannot be done or cannot happen.

example.ex: It was impossible for anyone to get in because no one knew the password...
example.tran: 因为没人知道密码,所以任何人都不可能进得去。

example.ex: He thinks the tax is impossible to administer...

example.tran: 你不该许诺做不到的事情。

example.ex: Keller is good at describing music – an almost impossible task to do well.
example.tran: 凯勒擅长描述音乐——这可是一项几乎难以做好的任务。

posc.def: The impossible is something which is impossible.
posc.tran: 不可能做到的事;难以完成的事

example.ex: They were expected to do the impossible...
example.tran: 他们被指望去完成难以完成的任务。

example.ex: No one can achieve the impossible.
example.tran: 这是不可能的事，没人能做到。

gramarinfo.label: oft <l>it</l> v-link ADJ to-inf/that, ADJ to-inf

example.ex: Mathematical physics is an almost impossibly difficult subject.
example.tran: 数学物理是一门难得超乎想象的学科。
认识绝对真理的不可能性

value.def: An impossible situation or an impossible position is one that is very difficult to deal with.

example.ex: The Government was now in an almost impossible position.
example.tran: 政府现在几乎陷入了进退维谷的境地。

value.def: If you describe someone as impossible, you are annoyed that their bad behaviour or strong views make them difficult to deal with.

example.ex: The woman is impossible, thought Frannie.
example.tran: 弗兰妮想,这个女人真让人受不了。

value.tran: 难以忍受的;让人受不了的
